Pseudocode:
Calculate the total and average rainfall per month over a period of years
Assign variables
First loop will ask for number of years(x)
Secondary loop will iterate the amount of months for number of years
Within second loop ask for inches of rain fall 
Calculate total rainfall and cumulative rainfall average
Print number of year and total months
Print total inches of rainfall
Print average rainfall per month for time span

Source code:
years = int(input ("How many years: "))
months = 12
total_rainfall = 0

for year in range(years):
    for month in range(months):
        m = float(input("inches of rain: "))
        total_rainfall += m
cumaverage = total_rainfall / (years * months)

print ("Total months: ", months * years)
print ("total inches of rainfall: ",total_rainfall)
print (f"Average rainfall was {cumaverage} inches of rain over a {months * years} period")


